From: Russell King <rmk+kernel@armlinux.org.uk>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2020 10:36:38 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] i2c: pxa: clear all master action bits in i2c_pxa_stop_message()
Git-commit: e81c979f4e071d516aa27cf5a0c3939da00dc1ca
Patch-mainline: v5.8-rc1
References: git-fixes

If we timeout during a message transfer, the control register may
contain bits that cause an action to be set. Read-modify-writing the
register leaving these bits set may trigger the hardware to attempt
one of these actions unintentionally.

Always clear these bits when cleaning up after a message or after
a timeout.

Signed-off-by: Russell King <rmk+kernel@armlinux.org.uk>
Signed-off-by: Wolfram Sang <wsa@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-pxa.c | 6 ++----
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-pxa.c b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-pxa.c
index db739cce93ac..a72d07bdb793 100644
--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-pxa.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-pxa.c
@@ -795,11 +795,9 @@ static inline void i2c_pxa_stop_message(struct pxa_i2c *i2c)
 {
 	u32 icr;
 
-	/*
-	 * Clear the STOP and ACK flags
-	 */
+	/* Clear the START, STOP, ACK, TB and MA flags */
 	icr = readl(_ICR(i2c));
-	icr &= ~(ICR_STOP | ICR_ACKNAK);
+	icr &= ~(ICR_START | ICR_STOP | ICR_ACKNAK | ICR_TB | ICR_MA);
 	writel(icr, _ICR(i2c));
 }
 
